The Story Bridge will be lit Orange to celebrate 2023 Australian Sikh Games.

The Australian Sikh Games are the premier sporting and cultural event for the Australian Sikh community. The Games are held every year in capital cities and major regional areas around Australia and coming to Brisbane in 2023. Over 4500 Athletes and 100,000 spectators from all over the country and overseas, including New Zealand, Malaysia, Singapore, Hong Kong, Canada and the U.K. come to participate in a wide array of traditional Indian and Australian sports and related events. The purpose of the event is to celebrate the cultural identity, preservation, building harmonious relations with other communities while celebrateing and engaging our large community and youth in sports.&nbsp;

This Light Up is organised by: Australian National Sikhs Sports &amp; Cultural Council QLD Inc.

